# Project: relagarden-astro (Astro v4+)

## Technical Stack
- Framework: Astro
- Language: TypeScript (Strict mode)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS (if installed) or Scoped CSS in .astro files
- Components: Astro Components (.astro) preferred

## Coding Rules
- Use Functional Components for any React/UI logic.
- Keep `.astro` files clean: separate Logic (frontmatter) and Template.
- Prioritize Astro's native components over client-side frameworks unless interactivity is required.
- Use `client:load` or `client:visible` directives only when necessary for performance.
- Image optimization: Always use the `<Image />` component from `astro:assets`.

## Directory Structure
- `src/components/`: Reusable UI elements.
- `src/layouts/`: Base HTML templates.
- `src/pages/`: File-based routing.
- `src/content/`: Content Collections for Markdown/MDX.

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., HeaderCard.astro)
- Utilities/Hooks: camelCase (e.g., useFormatDate.ts)
- CSS Classes: Tailwind standard or BEM if using raw CSS.